Crypto-method-getRandomValues.name: getRandomValues
Crypto-method-getRandomValues.summary: The Crypto.getRandomValues() method lets you get cryptographically strong random values. The array given as the parameter is filled with random numbers (random in its cryptographic meaning).
Crypto-method-getRandomValues.title: Crypto.getRandomValues()

dfn-Crypto.name: subtle
dfn-Crypto.summary: The Crypto.subtle read-only property returns a SubtleCrypto which can then be used to perform low-level cryptographic operations.
dfn-Crypto.title: Crypto.subtle

crypto-interface.name: Crypto
crypto-interface.summary: The Crypto interface represents basic cryptography features available in the current context. It allows access to a cryptographically strong random number generator and to cryptographic primitives.

nodejs.notes: Exported from the crypto module as webcrypto but not globally available.

crypto-interface.title: Crypto

dfn-CryptoKey.name: algorithm
dfn-CryptoKey.summary: The CryptoKey interface of the Web Crypto API represents a cryptographic key obtained from one of the SubtleCrypto methods generateKey(), deriveKey(), importKey(), or unwrapKey().
dfn-CryptoKey.title: CryptoKey

dfn-CryptoKey.name: extractable
dfn-CryptoKey.summary: The CryptoKey interface of the Web Crypto API represents a cryptographic key obtained from one of the SubtleCrypto methods generateKey(), deriveKey(), importKey(), or unwrapKey().
dfn-CryptoKey.title: CryptoKey

dfn-CryptoKey.name: type
dfn-CryptoKey.summary: The CryptoKey interface of the Web Crypto API represents a cryptographic key obtained from one of the SubtleCrypto methods generateKey(), deriveKey(), importKey(), or unwrapKey().
dfn-CryptoKey.title: CryptoKey

dfn-CryptoKey.summary: The CryptoKey interface of the Web Crypto API represents a cryptographic key obtained from one of the SubtleCrypto methods generateKey(), deriveKey(), importKey(), or unwrapKey().
dfn-CryptoKey.title: CryptoKey

dfn-CryptoKey.name: CryptoKey
dfn-CryptoKey.summary: The CryptoKey interface of the Web Crypto API represents a cryptographic key obtained from one of the SubtleCrypto methods generateKey(), deriveKey(), importKey(), or unwrapKey().
dfn-CryptoKey.title: CryptoKey

dfn-CryptoKeyPair.name: CryptoKeyPair
dfn-CryptoKeyPair.summary: The CryptoKeyPair dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents a key pair for an asymmetric cryptography algorithm, also known as a public-key algorithm.
dfn-CryptoKeyPair.title: CryptoKeyPair

SubtleCrypto-method-decrypt.name: decrypt
SubtleCrypto-method-decrypt.summary: The decrypt() method of the SubtleCrypto interface decrypts some encrypted data. It takes as arguments a key to decrypt with, some optional extra parameters, and the data to decrypt (also known as "ciphertext"). It returns a Promise which will be fulfilled with the decrypted data (also known as "plaintext").
SubtleCrypto-method-decrypt.title: SubtleCrypto.decrypt()

dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-deriveBits.name: deriveBits
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-deriveBits.summary: The deriveBits() method of the SubtleCrypto interface can be used to derive an array of bits from a base key.
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-deriveBits.title: SubtleCrypto.deriveBits()

dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-deriveKey.name: deriveKey
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-deriveKey.summary: The deriveKey() method of the SubtleCrypto interface can be used to derive a secret key from a master key.
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-deriveKey.title: SubtleCrypto.deriveKey()

dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-digest.name: digest
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-digest.summary: The digest() method of the SubtleCrypto interface generates a digest of the given data. A digest is a short fixed-length value derived from some variable-length input. Cryptographic digests should exhibit collision-resistance, meaning that it's hard to come up with two different inputs that have the same digest value.
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-digest.title: SubtleCrypto.digest()

SubtleCrypto-method-encrypt.name: encrypt
SubtleCrypto-method-encrypt.summary: The encrypt() method of the SubtleCrypto interface encrypts data.
SubtleCrypto-method-encrypt.title: SubtleCrypto.encrypt()

dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-exportKey.name: exportKey
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-exportKey.summary: The exportKey() method of the SubtleCrypto interface exports a key: that is, it takes as input a CryptoKey object and gives you the key in an external, portable format.
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-exportKey.title: SubtleCrypto.exportKey()

dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-generateKey.name: generateKey
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-generateKey.summary: Use the generateKey() method of the SubtleCrypto interface to generate a new key (for symmetric algorithms) or key pair (for public-key algorithms).
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-generateKey.title: SubtleCrypto.generateKey()

dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-importKey.name: importKey
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-importKey.summary: The importKey() method of the SubtleCrypto interface imports a key: that is, it takes as input a key in an external, portable format and gives you a CryptoKey object that you can use in the Web Crypto API.
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-importKey.title: SubtleCrypto.importKey()

dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-sign.name: sign
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-sign.summary: The sign() method of the SubtleCrypto interface generates a digital signature.
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-sign.title: SubtleCrypto.sign()

dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-unwrapKey.name: unwrapKey
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-unwrapKey.summary: The unwrapKey() method of the SubtleCrypto interface "unwraps" a key. This means that it takes as its input a key that has been exported and then encrypted (also called "wrapped"). It decrypts the key and then imports it, returning a CryptoKey object that can be used in the Web Crypto API.
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-unwrapKey.title: SubtleCrypto.unwrapKey()

dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-verify.name: verify
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-verify.summary: The verify() method of the SubtleCrypto interface verifies a digital signature.
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-verify.title: SubtleCrypto.verify()

dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-wrapKey.name: wrapKey
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-wrapKey.summary: The wrapKey() method of the SubtleCrypto interface "wraps" a key. This means that it exports the key in an external, portable format, then encrypts the exported key. Wrapping a key helps protect it in untrusted environments, such as inside an otherwise unprotected data store or in transmission over an unprotected network.
dfn-SubtleCrypto-method-wrapKey.title: SubtleCrypto.wrapKey()

subtlecrypto-interface.name: SubtleCrypto
subtlecrypto-interface.summary: The SubtleCrypto interface of the Web Crypto API provides a number of low-level cryptographic functions. Access to the features of SubtleCrypto is obtained through the subtle property of the Crypto object you get from Window.crypto.
subtlecrypto-interface.title: SubtleCrypto

dfn-GlobalCrypto.name: crypto
dfn-GlobalCrypto.summary: The read-only Window.crypto property returns the Crypto object associated to the global object. This object allows web pages access to certain cryptographic related services.
dfn-GlobalCrypto.title: Window.crypto
